    What makes a good description?
    Focus sentinel
    Close

    What makes a good description?

    The description outlines the scope of the agent, but doesn't impact the way the agent behaves.

    Consider the following factors to ensure that the AI model can best evaluate which agent to use to help your users:

    Domain expertise
    Clearly outline the domain or topic that the AI assistant specializes in. Use keywords that are related to the domain.
    Features and strengths
    Highlight unique features and strengths that the AI assistant possesses, and consider the user intentions when they prompt for the AI assistant.
    Limitations and scope
    Define the limits that the AI assistant has and its scope of knowledge. Defining limitations and scope might help avoid misunderstandings.
    Clear and simple language
    Opt for simple, straightforward language to convey the AI assistant's purpose and capabilities.

    HR policy document
    by basheeraazam02@gmail.com
    Options
    This agent provides 24/7 self-service support for all internal employee questions related to company policies, benefits, and administrative procedures. It processes natural language questions (e.g., "How many sick days do I have?") and retrieves the most accurate, up-to-date answer directly from the Employee Handbook and internal HR knowledge base.
